\v 2 \add From\add* that day¦134543, Sha'ul kept David \add with him\add*, and \add ≈wouldn't allow him to return¦134547 home\add*.
\v 3 Then¦134551 Yonatan and David \add ≈made an agreement together\add*, because \add @Yonatan\add* loved him as much as he loved himself.
\v 4 Yonatan took off the cloak that he was wearing and gave¦134566 it to David, along with his armour, his sword¦134571 and bow, and even his belt¦134577.
\v 5 David went¦134579 \add ≈on missions\add* wherever¦134582 Sha'ul sent¦134583 him and \add always\add* succeeded. Sha'ul \add ≈put him in charge of the warriors\add*, and that pleased¦134591 all the people¦134595, as well as Sha'ul's servants¦134598.
\s1 Sha'ul becomes envious of David
